        <h2>The ProAdjuster Approach to Shoulder Pain</h2>
        <p>Dr. Yager's evaluation begins with a thorough history and examination — assessing shoulder range of motion, muscle strength, joint stability, and neurological function in the arm. The ProAdjuster scan of the cervical and thoracic spine provides objective data about which spinal levels may be contributing to your symptoms.</p>
        <p>Treatment focuses on correcting spinal dysfunction in the cervical and thoracic regions using the gentle ProAdjuster instrument. By restoring normal motion to restricted segments, the treatment:</p>
        <ul>
